THis Command the Lord preſſeth with a threatning, that it may be known that he is in earneſt, and will reckon with men for the breaches of it: The ſcope of it, is, To have the Name of the Lord ſanctified, hallowed, and had in reverence by all his people, and ſo every thing eſchewed that may be dishonourable to that Holy Name, and which may make him, as it were, contemptible; this ſcope is clear from Levit. 22. verſe 32▪ Where having forbidden the prophaning of his Name, he addeth this poſitive precept, as oppoſite thereto; 

                        •
                     ut I will be hallowed among the Children of Iſrael; So then, its that he himſelf may be hallowed and had in reverence amongſt them, as Pſalm 89▪ 7. and 111. 9. And ſo this Command is much more extenſive then at firſt view it appeareth; the ſcope thereof, being to keep the heart in a holy awe and reverence of God, and ſo in a holy way of uſing, and reverent way of going about every thing which concerneth Him.
